    subgraph U3["Unit 3: Civil Liberties and Civil Rights"]
        U3S1["I know that the Bill of Rights is the first ten amendments to the Constitution"]
        U3S2["I know that the Bill of Rights originally restricted only the federal government not state governments"]
        U3S3["I know that the Fourteenth Amendment Due Process Clause is the basis for applying the Bill of Rights to states"]
        U3S4["I know what selective incorporation (applying the Bill of Rights to the states one right at a time) means — the case-by-case process of applying Bill of Rights protections to the states"]
        U3S5["I know that not all Bill of Rights provisions have been incorporated against the states"]
        U3S6["I know that the Establishment Clause prohibits government from establishing an official religion"]
        U3S7["I understand Engel v. Vitale ruling that school-sponsored prayer in public schools violates the Establishment Clause"]
        U3S8["I know that Engel v. Vitale held that government-directed prayer violates the separation of church and state"]
        U3S9["I know that the Free Exercise Clause is protecting the right to practice ones religion freely"]
        U3S10["I understand Wisconsin v. Yoder ruling that Amish families may exempt children from compulsory school after eighth grade"]
        U3S11["I know that Wisconsin v. Yoder held that free exercise of religion outweighed the states interest in education"]
        U3S12["I understand the tension between the Establishment Clause and the Free Exercise Clause"]
        U3S13["I know that the First Amendment is protecting freedom of speech"]
        U3S14["I understand Schenck v. United States ruling that speech creating a clear and present danger is not protected"]
        U3S15["I understand the clear and present danger test as a standard for when government may limit speech"]
        U3S16["I understand Tinker v. Des Moines ruling that students retain First Amendment rights in public schools"]
        U3S17["I know that student speech can be limited only if it causes substantial disruption to the school environment"]
        U3S18["I know categories of unprotected speech, including incitement, true threats, fighting words, and obscenity"]
        U3S19["I understand the ongoing balancing test between protecting free speech and maintaining public order and safety"]
        U3S20["I understand the distinction between content-based and content-neutral restrictions on speech"]
        U3S21["I know that symbolic speech such as flag burning and armbands is generally protected by the First Amendment"]
        U3S22["I know that the First Amendment is protecting freedom of the press"]
        U3S23["I understand New York Times Co. v. United States ruling against prior restraint (government censorship before something is published) of the Pentagon Papers publication"]
        U3S24["I know what prior restraint (government censorship before something is published) means — government censorship prohibiting speech or publication before it occurs"]
        U3S25["I know that prior restraint (government censorship before something is published) carries a heavy presumption of unconstitutionality under the First Amendment"]
        U3S26["I know that the Second Amendment is protecting the right to keep and bear arms"]
        U3S27["I understand McDonald v. City of Chicago ruling that the Second Amendment applies to state and local governments"]
        U3S28["I understand the ongoing debate between individual gun rights and government authority to regulate firearms"]
        U3S29["I know that McDonald v. City of Chicago is an example of selective incorporation (applying the Bill of Rights to the states one right at a time) of the Second Amendment"]
        U3S30["I know Fourth Amendment protections against unreasonable searches and seizures"]
        U3S31["I understand the exclusionary rule — illegally obtained evidence can't be used in court"]
        U3S32["I understand the warrant requirement and probable cause (reasonable belief that a crime occurred) standard under the Fourth Amendment"]
        U3S33["I know Fifth Amendment protections, including due process (fair legal procedures), protection from double jeopardy, and self-incrimination"]
        U3S34["I understand how the Fifth Amendment due process (fair legal procedures) clause protects individuals from arbitrary federal government action"]
        U3S35["I know the Sixth Amendment rights, including speedy trial, impartial jury, and right to counsel"]
        U3S36["I understand Gideon v. Wainwright ruling that states must provide attorneys to defendants who cannot afford them"]
        U3S37["I know that Gideon v. Wainwright incorporated the Sixth Amendment right to counsel against the states"]
        U3S38["I know that the Eighth Amendment prohibits excessive bail, excessive fines, and cruel and unusual punishment"]
        U3S39["I understand ongoing debates about the application of cruel and unusual punishment to the death penalty"]
        U3S40["I understand how due process (fair legal procedures) protections balance the need for government power with individual rights"]
        U3S41["I understand the right to privacy as derived from multiple amendments including the First, Third, Fourth, Fifth, and Ninth"]
        U3S42["I know what Roe v. Wade is — establishing a constitutional right to privacy regarding abortion"]
        U3S43["I understand the ongoing debate over the scope and limits of the right to privacy"]
        U3S44["I understand the Fourteenth Amendment Equal Protection Clause as requiring states to provide equal treatment under the law"]
        U3S45["I understand how the Equal Protection Clause has been used to combat racial, gender, and other forms of discrimination"]
        U3S46["I understand Brown v. Board of Education ruling that racial segregation in public schools violates equal protection"]
        U3S47["I know that Brown overturned the separate but equal doctrine established in Plessy v. Ferguson"]
