        U3S53["I understand the Civil Rights Act of 1964 as prohibiting discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex, or national origin"]
        U3S54["I understand the Voting Rights Act of 1965 as prohibiting racial discrimination in voting and eliminating literacy tests"]
        U3S55["I know what Title IX of the Education Amendments of 1972 is — prohibiting sex-based discrimination in federally funded education"]
        U3S56["I understand how government legislation has responded to social movements to expand civil rights protections"]
        U3S57["I understand how the womens rights movement used the Equal Protection Clause to challenge gender discrimination"]
        U3S58["I understand the tension between majority rule and protection of minority rights in a democratic system"]
        U3S59["I understand how the judiciary serves as a protector of minority rights against potential tyranny of the majority"]
        U3S60["I know what affirmative action means — policies that consider race or gender to benefit underrepresented groups"]
        U3S61["I understand the ongoing debate over whether affirmative action promotes equality or constitutes reverse discrimination"]
